id.description: The ID used to identify this component in callbacks

setProps.description: Dash-assigned callback that should be called whenever properties change

selectionType.description: The selection type - may be atom, residue or chain

backgroundColor.description: Property to change the background color of the molecule viewer

backgroundOpacity.description: Property to change the backgroun opacity - ranges from 0 to 1

styles.description:
Property that can be used to change the representation of
the molecule. Options include sticks, cartoon and sphere

modelData.description:
The data that will be used to display the molecule in 3D
The data will be in JSON format 
and should have two main dictionaries - atoms, bonds

atomLabelsShown.description: Property to either show or hide labels

selectedAtomIds.description: Property that stores a list of all selected atoms

labels.description: labels corresponding to the atoms of the molecule

onRenderNewData.description:
Callback to re-render molecule viewer
when modelData is changed

onChangeSelection.description:
Callback to change append selectedAtomIds 
when a selection is made
